overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate its adherence to the provided Statement of
  Work and detailed questionnaire specification. The assistant conducted a
  thorough analysis, identifying several critical gaps and then proceeded to
  implement the highest priority items. This included integrating a 1-10
  severity scale for tiredness, complete with safety warnings for high scores,
  and enhancing the report generation to accurately detect and provide tailored
  guidance for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep
  Syndrome. These updates involved modifying data types, validation schemas, UI
  components, and report generation logic to ensure a more robust and clinically
  relevant assessment for users.
